import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import shap

df = pd.read_csv("/Users/fizza/path/to/Gly-data y1.csv")

def clean_target(val):
    if str(val).strip() in ['xx', 'xx', 'xx']:
        return 0.01
    try:
        return float(val)
    except:
        return np.nan

df['y1'] = df['y1'].apply(clean_target)
df = df.dropna(subset=['y1'])

target_col = 'y1'
feature_cols = [col for col in df.columns if col.startswith('x')]
X = df[feature_cols].copy()
y = df[target_col]

for col in X.select_dtypes(include=['object', 'category']):
    X[col] = LabelEncoder().fit_transform(X[col].astype(str))

X = X[list(custom_names.keys())]
X.rename(columns=custom_names, inplace=True)

model = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=200, random_state=42)
model.fit(X, y)
